headline: Getting to the Moon or Mars? Musk and Bezos Tackle Space Travel’s Refueling Problem
summary: Spacecraft that could fuel up in orbit would be less weighted down at liftoff and fly deeper into space; making those refills happen is a big challenge for SpaceX and Blue Origin.

headline: Why green aviation fuel failed to take off
summary: For those flying south this summer, the prospect of “green fuel” one day powering their planes down to the south of France or the Med may mean a little less guilt over their climate-destroying air travel.
